{"/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_thirteen_ver01/data/sn87062268/00175043470/1908031501/0616.xml":{"full_text":"c\nII\nTV T\nmi K S i M\ni ct 7 VS T j t Pt f\n4 ll1E SAdOLA TOURKL SuNDAY MORNING MARCH 1 1908\nJ Ibe r lmiurola1Jtmfnal\n1 ww r u W im i\ni I 5\n1 l DAILY WEEKLY SUNDAY\nI\nyt jgTJRTMf EVE MOlt IIIXI XDZlI j\nair\nI THE JOURNAL dOMPANII\n1 II\nFRANK L MAYES PSllt aslGe nel Mo9 I\nI W flfL rwn WflnSflrnrcJn flj j 1j njuu na n tr rur W WJj\nMEMBER THE AssoelA TED 1 PRESS\nPIfESSJ\n1 SUBSCRIPTION RATES i\nOne y ooJi 66 Grse Moatfe 45\nSix Mcnths 3 56 One Week oo S oo 10 i\nTroe 1 35 Weekly Edition er yer1 Cit\nrnJw WJW r r rr fl L SW t fl L flLhIlJtLW\nI Thy Only Fanaacot Newspaper Fri Wkfcti a Datallsd f\nCirculation Statamont Can SB SectiUtJfL\nI\na p n Lr S njs n r j nr\nM Sale on Trittx j\nI 1 T\nand at all News Stand I\nw L JPJUUL ir\n1 Phones Editorial Rooms 38 Business Office 1500\nwwJwtrr WflteWLr WLtfl wrr w\nOffices Journal Bu4Irflng Cerner In4an ono1a and DoLuna Sts\n1\nl f r\nPBNSAJOOilJA FLORIDA UN DAY MORINTNG MAIIGH 15 19G8\nI Pensacola and\nIt the Tourists\nI The attractions of Pen cola as a\nlit tourist resort during the winter\nmonths have been discovered by the\nt northern public without much help\non the part of the people of Pensacola\nWe have a fine northern colony\nher now nice people without excep\nI tion t spending the winter with us\nand spending money too and it we\nt\nwould properly advertise the city and\nits advantages through the northern\nstates we would get very many more\nI winter residents from that section\nI than we do now We probably have\na hundred or a hundred and fifty\npeople in Pensacola now from the\nnorth who are here to escape the\np winter rigors of their home climate\nThey have been here from one to\nthree months and will be here for\nI several weeks longer Each of them\nspends at least 150 while he is in\nr Pensacola that much hard cash put\ninto circulation right here\nSuppose we have a thousand such\nI\ntourists every winter It would mean\n160000 added annually to our wealth\nWhat investment could possibly pay\nbetter for the amount invested And\nwe have to invest nothing beyond ad\nvertising the advantages of Peusacola\nas a winter resort and providing the\nnecessary facilities to make the tour\nists coinfortarole after they get her\nand give them a good time\nThese northern tourists to Pensa\ncola are a very quiet modest and un\nassuming set but they are almost in\nvariably superior people the kind\nthat make the nation strong in the i\nbody of its citizenship and they dont\ncome here to seek vice nor dissipa\ntion nor frivolity They love our\nbland and restful climate in such\nmarked contrast with the one they\nleft and they are here to recuperate\ntheir energies get away from the snow\nand ice and blizzards and put in sev\neral months of solid comfort\nEspecially do they love the grand\nfarstretching bay with its clear salt\nneater sparkling under agenial south\nern sun and they want to bathe In\nit and dabble around like children in\nits clean healthrestoring waters\nThey want to go to it every day and\nthey want the transportation the bath\nhouses and other facilities which they\nhave a right to expect under the cir\ncumstances and without worrying\nI every day to get them\nWe doubt if there are such facili\nI ties up to the standard required and\nIt would certainly pay local enterprise\nto provide them Your northern\ns\ntourist always pays his way ch erful\ny but he wants good service and is I\na vigorous and honest kicker if he\nI\ndon get it Pensacola has nsgecteil\n1 this large asset of the northern I\nwfnter tourist travel and It Is high\ntime that she was waking up rc her\nopportunity in this direction If we\ni would advertise like the East Coast\nand then provide the hotel boating\nand bathing facilities to accommo\ndate our patrons we could easly i\n3 toring a thousand northern people\nhere every winter to stay for several\nI months for we have every advantage\nj of the East Coast in point of natural\nattractions\nThe Journal would like to hear\nfrom some northern tourist nov j\nour city on this question Our col\numns are open to him Let him speak\nfreely and tell just what he would\nlike to have here that he misses\nS Some of the Florida papers con\ntinue to fiercely denounce the railroad\ncommission because of Its recent rul\ning to the effect that transportation\ncould not be exchanged for advertis\nI r ing And yet not one of these apers\nt has addressed itself to the merits of\nthe case and attempted to controvert\nI the facts and reasoning upon wMoh\ntthe ruling of the commission was\n1 ibased That is not the way to extend\nr newspaper dnfluence nor to make the\nF editorial page a real factor in the dls\ncu slon of public questions and tjho\nM IWj b1\nf\na\nNever Such Chances for\nYoung Men as Now\nWe talj about hard times and the\noppression of pooled capital and the\nrich grinding the face of the poor\nand monopoly shutting out the small\ndealer and the diminishing chances\nfor the ordinary citizen ot limited\nmeans to take the initiative in any\ncommercial industrial enterprise\nWe dont deny it there is truth in it\nbut all the same there never was a\nperiod in the worlds history when\ncompetent men who have learned to\ndo one thing thoroughly well or who\nwere strong in executive ability were\nso much in demand as they are now\nThis Is an age of corporations and\nnot all the politics can stay their\nprogress and the corporations are\nhunting fopgoodmen competent men\nto tafce ehaiige ot the various branches\nof their business at salaries away\nahead of those paid in former eras\nof our development\nIt is idle to protest against the de\ncree of evolution The corporations\nare here and here to stay and to\ngrow stronger every year The peo\npie must and will regulate them and\nkeep them in their just relation to\nthe body politic but assuming that\nto be true and it is truewe must\nprovide the men to operate these cor\nporations in all their numerous di\nvisions and subdivisions It will\ntake thousands of them highly train\ned to do soand here lies the hope\nof the country especially of ibe\nSouth\nWe are reminded to say this be\ncause we see in the dispatcbxM that\nGeneral Manager Garrett of the Sea\nboard Air Line has been called to\nthe management of the Atlantic\nCoast Line a greater corporation be\ncause of his remarkable executive\nability Garrett started out a plain\neveryday Mississippi boy honest in\ntelligent energetic and ambitious and\nnow he is at the top Running down\nthrough the various grade we find\nI similar types commanding fine saJa I\nries and doing much better than they\ncould have over done on their indi\nvidual initiative in individual enter\nprises\nAnd as with railroads so with the\nother numberless forms of corporate\nenterprisethe man who can do one\nthing well is in demand all the time\nand at good pay Old things have\npassed away and we live in a new era\nunder new conditions but now as\never it is the man of character who\nI wins but and under the dominion of\nI the corporation there are more and\nricher prizes hung up to Be secured\nby worthy men than ever before\n1NV r In the worlds history was there\nsuch an insistent demand for\nI first class men in all the num\nberless forms of human activity\nas now But they must be high\nstahuard men sctoer industrious\ntrustworthy highly skilled and special\nized The time has passed when the\nt\nclever feller willing to work at any\nthing and able to do nothing well\nhad the call His day Is over The\nworld demands a higher grade of\nworkmen now and it will pay tEem\nbetter than they were ever paid be\nfore\nThe Journal is publishing all the\nlive news it can collect from Its ex\nchanges and other sources about the\npolitical c campaign in Florida but It\nmust be confessed that it doesnt make\nvery sensational reading There Is a\nlack ol interest This is the result of\nfactional politics in which all the can\ndhJates belong to the same political\nparty and it Is only a question be\ntween friends of getting up to the\ntrough We dQnt want any acandal in\nstate politics and we see no pr prospect\nof any but It does seem that nothing\nless wtill arouse the great democracy\nof Florida If 1t gets much worse we\nshall insist that To Collins or the\nTallahassee True Democrat shall get\na seasons lease on the frightful Brow\nard machine In state politics and\nake the road with a tent show with\nAIoW lWtB W M iMw4\n1 s\nJ\n\nv S\nin order that the people may fully un\nderstand just how horribly oppressed\nthey are Barnum once said that the\nAmerican people 10Ctobe hum\nbugged and John is is1 such deadly\nearnest about the machine that we\nbelieve he could make a roaxing suc\ncess of it without any intent to hum\nbug\nL VOX POPULI J\nMUST EITHER BEE STEAL OR\nSTARVE IF OUT OF WORK\nEditor Pensacola Journal\nFiease allow me space in your Vox\nPopuH column for thefolloowingrletter\nIn your editorial on Mr Bran as\nanswering the question of what is a\nman to do in a financial panic who is\nout of employment and starving you\nlaud him on his clear and logical\nanswer when in fact he failed to\nanswer it at all He did give a good\nanswer to what we must do for the\nman also he gave good advice as how\ntp prevent such an occurrence\nNow I do not claim to be as wise\nas Mr Bryan nor as wise as Mr\nMayes both are men of minds that\nare ahead of the times men that un\nderstand political economy and cur\nrent issues better than I possibly can\nbut there is a difference between\ntheory and practice and the many\nwriters on the subject seem to be so\nfar from the scene until they are\nlike Miss Quacken writing about\nsomething of which they know noth\ning or of which they have only skim\nmed the surface\nIf I understand the question it is\nwhat isa man to do who is out of\nemployment in a financial panic and\nis starving The very question car\nries with it the assumption that the\nman Js out of work because he can\nget no work to do and that includes\neven carpets to beat Why For\nthe reason set forth in the question\nthat there is a financial panic and\npublic works are at a standstill and\nthat those who employ help when con\nditions are normal are no longer em\nploying help because they do not need\nit The manufacturer shuts the mill\ndown because he cannot sell the\ngoods the railroads laYoff their\ncrews because there Is ho traffic the\nmerchant lays off some of his help\nhe does not need for if men are out\nof employment they cannot buy goods\nand have plenty time to beat the car\npets cut wood and do the gardening\nNor Is Socialism ananswer It le\na preventive or might be a prevent\nive if practicable which is very\ndoubtful Thomas Moms at the com\nmencement of the sixteenth century\nadvocated Socialism that is he de\nnounced or condemned individual I\nproperty in terms more de8nffe than\nthe Socialist of today does Or can\nand since his day many have advo\ncated the same theory and with what\nresults There arestili classes there\nare still labor and capital and there\nwill be as longas there are men for\nall men are not equal all men have\nnot the same capacity nor can an act\nor a legislative body make them so\nSocialism is wiser than Jehovah\nfor did he not Cl eat roasters and\nservants Has He not said through\nhis inspired servants servantsibbDe\nyour masters\nBut let us get back to the question\nand see if it can be answered and\nwhat the answer is There can be\nbut one answer to it What isa man\nto do who is out of work in a finan\ncial panic and is starving He must\neither beg steal or starve\nL A SAiMPUEY\nCentury Fla\n\nPENSACOLA AND\nPENSAGOLIANS\nNew Industry Near Pensacola\nit is reportedthat fin acres of cu\ncumbers have been planted by truck\nfarmers north of Pensaiola and should\nthe crop be a profitableonethecoming\nyear will witness a much largtir acre\nage The planters closed before they\nplanted the crop with a prominent\nvegetable dealer not only to handle\nthe crop but also to pick and market\nthe caicumbers In fact the crop was\nsold before it was planted and it is\nthe intention to ship the vegetables\nin carload lots as xiijs js the only ba\ns upon which the buyers would con\nsent to sending experienced men to\nlook after the picking and shipping\nThe cucumbers are to be packed inic\nand placed in refrigerator cars and\nas the planting has Just been finished\nthey will be in he early markets\nThe growing of cucumbers is some\nwhat of a departure especially a\n1arge scale Iive pajc Democrat\nBernard Talks for Pensacola\nTh railroad is absolutely certain\nof construction Boone day or other\nremarked lTB S Bernard of the\nPensacola Journal who is spending\nthe day In Meridian apd it isup to\nthe people of Meridian and Pensacola\nto build the line with as little delay\nas possible\nMr Bernard represents in a busi\nness capacity the Journal both in Pen\nsacola and in the outside territory\nu\nana nas a spiensua grasp on the value\nof a road connecting the Queen City\nof Mississippi aud the great Florida\nport would prove not only to the cities\nto be linked together but the vast ter\nritory lying between\nWe have worked hand in Pensa\ncola for the road he remarked and\nMeridian may depend OIL us to carry\nour share of the responsibilities ot I I\nbuilding Our people are anxious for I\na direct connection and I am hope\nful it will not be long before through\ntraffic and passenger travel between\nMeridian and Pensacola will be as\nconvenient travel from your city to\nNew Orleans or Mobile S\nBernard spent today lathe city\nand expressed himself as pleased at\nthe eplendid progress Meridian ha\nmade Meridian BUss Star\nHas Center of the Stage\nJohn Beard and his disfranchise\nment plank are now occupying the\ncenter of the Florida political stage\nPalatka TimesHerald\nNothing But Politics Left\nPensacolas Mardi Gras the state\nfair at Tampa and the midwinter ex\nposition at Jacksonville are all over\nand there is nothing left in the way\nQt iff TtiHifiBTfjUMB t Wit OlitlCS TJlfe\nj\n\nS\n\nt\nI\nBEARDS CAMPAIGN i\nli T FOR U S SENATE\ni v\nHow the Persacola Candidate la Faring Through the State\n\nAll Busy Canvassing\nLamar Bearxl and Fletcher are bus\nily engaged in canvassing the state in\nthe interest of their respective candl\ndacles for the senate and the friends\nof each seem to be on1identor a\nfavorable outcome Each has arge\nand interested audiences much ap\nplause and friendly comments by the\nlocal press These straws indicate\nthat the wind are variable Tampa\nTimes\nDates In Lake City And Ft White\nHon John S Beard candidate for\nthe United States senate will speak\nin Lake City on March 20 and at Ft\nWhite on March 21Lake City Cit\nizen Reporter\nA Quartette of Candidates\nWhen Fletcher Bryan ILamar and\nBeard meet injoint debate there\nshould be a sufficient flow of elo\nquence to drown the cries of the\nknockers and other calamity howl\ners Palatka TimesHerald\nr\nThe Lines Olosely Drawn\nWe heard four men asked the ques\ntion this week as to who was the\nstrongest man for United States sena\ntor in Jackson county and the strange\npart of it was that none could or\nwould say One did venture to say\nthat it stood between Beard Bryan\nFletcher and Lamar This was a very I\nindefinite answer and shows that the\nlines for this important position have I\nnot as yet been closely drawn Ma\nrianna TimesCourier\nLoudly Applauded At Key West\nIn answer to a call of the demo\ncratic executive committee quite a\nnumber of democratic voters gathered\nat Ayalas corner last night to listen\nto the addresses of Hon John S\nBeard candidate for United States I\nsenator and Hon Jefferson i\nBrowne candidate for governor\nHon W Hunt Harris opened the\nmeeting and most heartily endorsed\nMr Beard in his candidacy for the\njsenate He their introduced Mr\nBeard who spoke for an hour dealing\nfirst with his own campaign and later\nwith national issues Mr Beard is a\nfluent and an exceedingly pleasing\nI speaker and his address last night\nwas of the nature to appeal strongly\n1to the voters of this county He made\nno promises which he cannot consci\nentiously and constantly fulfill in part\nif he did not do all that he promised\nhe would violate his oath of office\nThe crowd listened attentively to\nhis remarks aneT applauded loudly at\nfrequent interyals Mr Beard has the\noutspoken support of many prominent I\ncitizens and he will undoubtedly get\na large vote hereKey West Citizen\nWould Be An Honor to Florida\nHon John S Beard of Pehsacola\ncandidate for the United States sen\nate and Hon Jeff B Browne of Key\nWest candidate for governor spoke\nto a large audience at the courthouse\nlast Monday night and it was the\nopening gun of the1 campaign in this\ncounty Long before oclock every\nseat in the courthouse was occupied\nbv voters and ladies to hear these two\ndistinguished sons of Florida speak\nThat venerable lifelong democrat Dr\nH BT racer presided the meet\ning and introduced the speakers Mr\nBrowne spoke first occupying one\nhour and fifteen minutes time iMr\nBrowne has been In public life in the\nstate for a number of years several\ntimes a member of the senate from\nshould be warm enough from now un\ntil the primaries are pulled off to sat\nisfy the appetites of the average cit\nizen Marianna TimesCourier\nJudge Laney Is Busy\nJudge Chas H Laney of Pensa\ncola was handshaking around here\nTuesday Judge Laney isa candi\ndate for congress and while here did\nnot let the grassgrow und r his feet\nThe judge met with a number of old\ntime friends who formerly used to be\nneighbors of his in Alabama Laurel\nHill Southern Home\nWill Soon Rival New Orleans\nI\niTank Mayes has been courting\nthe Queen of the Mardi Gras this\nweek Pensacolas big annual event\nwill soon be as important as that of\nNew Orleans fit Petersburg Inde\npendent\nIt Was the Biggest Ever\nPensacolas Mardi Gras was the\nbiggest ever and all who attended\nclaim they got their moneys worth\nJIolmes County Advertiser\n3\n3POLITICS\nPOLITICS AND\nPOLITICIANS\nJ\nWould Make Good Officer\nThe True Democrat offers to its\nbrethren of the state press for their\nconsideration the name of Hon T J J\nApple ard of Lake City for the po\nsition of State Comptroller Like\nother newspaper men of Florida he\nhas given considerable of his time\nand his limited means to those things\nthat tend to the developmentof the\nstate iHis recent exhibit at the tate\nfair Tampa of the resources of the\nnorthern section of the state in\nplacing his own countys resources\non exhibition should give him the\nsupport of every man Politically\ndurng a public life of over twenty\nyears he has been clean and upright\nXo man can point to a dishonorable\nact of his He would be a strong\nman and would make a good officer\nWhat say our brethren of the state\npress Who seconds themotion of\nthe True Democrat Tallahassee\nTrue Democrat\nStrong Boost for Good Man\nThus far in the political campaign\nnow in progress In this state we have\nmade no suggestion of candidates for\nany of the offices to be filled There\nIs never a dearth of candidates when\never any officeis to be filled aaaV we i j\nT\nia\nv\nC vS\ni i\nf\nKey West anf for one term was pres I\nident of that body He was also elect\ned railroad commissioner and was\nelected and acted as chairman of that\nbody until he resigned a year ago\nAlong the line of his platform which\nhas been published he spoke to the\nVolusia people his candidacy and of\nhis desire to be elected governor or\nthe state of Florida His platform is\na good one and appeals direct to the\npeople in their interests From the be\nginning Air Browne in his address\nimpressed you as being frank honest\nand sincere and we believe that he\nis and thatthere is none of the dem\nagogue in him but he means what he\nsays and will carry out the state pol I\nicies he advocates\nMr Beard followed Mr Browne\nspeaking for nearly an hour and a hair\nHe is one of the brilliant thinkers and\norators of Florida a mo3t forceful\nspeaker and his every word impresses\nyou with his honesty and sincerity\nHe advocates the complete elimina\ntion of the negro exercising any\nfranchise right that they have never\nbeen constitutionally given that right\nand offered convincing argument in\nSupport this contention Mr Beards\nplatform as we have stated before is\naU in the interest of the masses It\nwas published in these columns some\nmonths ago He wants state prohibi\ntion us Mr Browne does and wants\na federal statute which will prohibit\ntransportation companies taking whis\nkle into prohibition states or into dry\ncounties He is in sympathy with and\nadvocates the reforms as promulgated\nby the great Nebraskan and a nation\nal law that will absolutely curb every\ngrasping corporation the country\nMr Beard will be a power In the sen\natorial race he ismaking an honor\nable manly and lair canvass of the\nstate and it is said is gaining\nstrength fast throughout every section\nof Florida As a United States sena\ntor he would be an honor to Florida\nand her people\nBoth Mesa Browne and Beard\nmade favorable impressions among\nour people and gained many friends\nand supporters by their visit to Vol\nusaa VoluBia County Record\nRoundly Cheered at Mi mi\nA crowd of severaJ hundred per\nsons tie great majority of them qual\nified voters turned out Saturday night\nto hear the addresses of Hon John b\nBeard candidate for United States\nsenator and Hon Jefferson B Browne\naspirant totbe governorship and\nthoroughly enjoyed the same u\nMr Browne spoke first and devot\ned the better part of his time to rc\ncitflng ibiS platform and dwelling\nthereon He promised the people It\nelected a fair honest and impartial\ngovernment in so tar as his efforts\ncould go and made a hit as was\nevinced by the frequent and generous\napplause\nMr Beard spoke last and paid par\nticular attention to his fifteenth\namendment plankdisfranchising the\nnegro and advanced the argument\nthat the equal rights of the negro\nwere never ratified in the constitution\nof the United States He clalmed to\nhave documentary evidence of that\nfact and it was evident that it is the\nintention of Mr Beard if elected\nUnited States senator to bring the\nquestion to issue before the supreme\ncourt of the United States\nBach speaker consumed about an\nhour and at the conclusion of tilt\nmeeting were roundly cheered and\ngreetedMiami Metropolis\ndo not believe men should be urged\nby their friends to become candidates\nexcept in certain cases for instance\nwhen one is especially qualified to\nfill an office and is too modest to push\nhimself forward or for some similar\nreason In such cases we think the\noffice should seek the man and his\nfriends should pushhim forwardEn\ntertaining these views we make our\nfirst suggestion of a candidate in nam\ning Editor M F Hetherington of the\nLakeland News for state superintend\nent of public instruction He is\nyotyig full of energy thoroughly edu\ncated and in every way qualified to\nmake an ideal superintendentBar\ntow CourierInformant\nLooks Mighty Like Stockton\nFor Floridas next chief executive\nit looks mighty like John N C Stock\nton and we are not crosseyed\neither Hotmes County Advertiser\nWill Be Next Governor\nx It is generally conceded that Hon\nJ N C Stockton will be the next\ngovernor of Florida He is undoubt\nedly the favorite with Alachua county\nVoters though all the other candi\ndates for the high office have ardent\nsupporters in this county Those who I\nhave known Mr Stockton for many I\nyears feel assured that he will make\na good governor and they are going\nto show their faith In him by voting\nfor himrGainesville Sun\nf\nNo Brighter in Congress\nSay all the mean things about Clark\nyou please but we had just as well\ntell you right now that there isnt\na brighter man in either house of\ncongress today nor has there been\nfor several years past Jacksonville\nFloridian\nSubscribe for The Journal\nIn times financial squeam\nishness a clear brain and steady\nnerve are at a premium Drink\nP08TU\nTheres a Reason\ni\np\nj\nEnAJAAr\nCONCLUSIONS\nChina to Pajr Japan ldOOQ\nand Retain Arms That\nWere Seized\nBy Associated Pre\nPeking March 14Ihe negotia\ntions looking to a settlement the\ndifficulty between China and Japan\nout of the seizure by China of the\nJapanese steamer Tatsu Maru are\nmaking favorable progress\nThe Chinese foreign board today\napproved the draft of a document in\nwhich China acepts the proposals\nmade iby Japan yesterday China will\npay Japan 21000 yen about 10700\nand retain the arms that form the\ncargo of the Tatsu Maru and she\nwill also pay about 10000 taels de\nmurrage on the steamer It is ex\npected that the Tatsu Maru will be\nreleased March 1G\nIn additioh Japan agrees to adopt\nand enforc strictregulations to pre\nvent future traffic in arms and am\nmunition fromJapan into China but\nshe refuses to include the territory\nof Mlacao in this limitation\nChina will soontake up negotiations\nwith Portugal regarding the contra\nband traffic at Macao She hopes\nthat an accurate deliniation of Portu\ngese waters at Macao now will be\nObtained and that the gambling for\nwhich Macao is notorious as well as\nthe smuggling done through that\nport may be materially restricted\nlABORERS HinT\nINN Y STREETS\nMany Shots Fired by Mem\n1\nbers of Two Teamsters\nOrganizations\nBy Associated Press\nNew York March 14 rForty or\nmore shots were fired and one man\nwounded tonight in a street riot be\niween members of the United Team\nstera association and International\nBrotherhood of Teamsters\nThe disorder was the climax of ill\nfeeling precipitated by the discharge\nof United Teamsters and substitution\nor teamsters from the International\nunion bvau eaSt 5der truck man\nPolice reserves quelled the diSturb\nance alter imakins three arrests\nBACK TO DAYS\nOF WILD WEST\nOklahoma Bandits Hold a\nPosse at Bay and Bat\ntle is Expected\n1\nBy Associated Press\nWann Okla March 14rbe three\nbandits wljo auccesaf ully held up the\nBank of Tyro Cansas yesterday\nwere completely surrounded tonight\nseven miles south of here and are\nholding their pursuers at bay\nA large number of men armed with\nlong range suns have gone to the as\nsistance of the posse tonight it is\nbelieved the robbers will attempt to\nbreak through the sentinels and a\nbattle is expected\nKAISER LIKED AM\nBASSADOR TOWER\n1\nBv Associated Press\nBerlin March 14Emperor Wil\nliam who last night dined With Char\nlemagne Tower the American ambas\nsador has again expressed his appre\nciation of Mr Towers labors in Ber\nlin His majesty was Informed dur\ning j course of the dinner that\nFrederick OatrldweH the American\nviceconsul here was Jo sail today for\ner1caHe thereupon approached\nMr CauldlwelL and told him he had\na message for President Roosevelt\nTell your president Emperor\nWilliam said that I am very angry\nwith him for accepting Mr Towers\nresignation\nThe emperor has presented each of\nthe Tower children with a photo\ngraph pf himself bearing his own sig\nnature and also pfctures of Princess\nVictoria\nMAYBE PEACE\nIN MOROCCO\nBy Associated Press\nIMadrid March 14 Official confirm\nation has been received here from\nMorocco of the report that Mule\nHafid the insurgent Sultan has sub\nmitted peace proposals to AbElAzlz\nthe suljtan of record It is rumored\nthat an arrangement may be made\nby which ilulaiHaifld and his lieuten\nants will be furnished money for an\nindefinite pilgrimage to Mecca In\nother words that they will be paid to\nleave the country\nBRUSH WITH TRIESMEtf\nBy Associated Press I\nOran Algeria March 14A de\ntachment of French troops reconoiter\ning in the Sriouti region has had a\nsharp brush with the tribesmen in\nwhich an officer was filled and two\nmen Wounded i\nt\n4\nV\n1\nOUTRAGES Uf\nN1GHT RID Em\n1\nBurning Property Contin\nues in Kentucky To\nbacco Districts\nBy Associated Press\nVer